net.kuujo.vertigo.cluster.data

Interface WatchableAsyncMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - The map key type.
    V - The map value type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AsyncMap<K,V>

    public interface WatchableAsyncMap<K,V>
extends AsyncMap<K,V>
    Watchable asynchronous map.

    This is an extension of the AsyncMap interface that supports map key events. Types that implement this interface will trigger event handlers when data changes in the map. Note that events can be received from anywhere in the cluster, so the async map events system is distributed.

    Author:
    Jordan Halterman
